The paper deals with the application of cumulative prospect theory (CPT) to reinforcement learning (RL) settings, which involves both prediction and control. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which is the primary focus of the paper. The paper also involves decision-making under uncertainty, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the optimization of randomized policies, which is a topic in control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the usefulness of CPT-based criteria in a traffic signal control application, which involves game theory (cs.GT).
